{
  "stem": "5810.3",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And I knew that something very big was happening and it had to happen.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And of course, the news was telling us that they were advancing.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And then came screaming, and joy, and flags were- were coming out of the balconies and the windows and all of that.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Then I finally ventured out.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I saw very near this famous Legale Duneaux Station, the tanks rolling in with the British soldiers and the American soldiers and all of that.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We knew it was liberation time, but then what?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Who was I?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Where were my brothers and sisters?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "What were we going to do?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "How were we going to live?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Where were we going to go?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "What money would we use?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It wasn't over.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Then of course, we still had hopes that some of my family had survived.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We, of course, had then-- by then, heard about concentration camps, and the gassing, and the burning, and all of that.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So we were hopeful.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "In fact, for probably three years, for three years after liberation, there was a Jewish organization in Belgium that had an office that would receive the names of the-- [SIGHS] I don't know what to call Holocaust survivors-- but they were coming back to their homes.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they would post these names daily.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So my mother, from the day of liberation to probably two to three years after that, every day went to that office and sat with other people that had survived, and sat there waiting for those names to show up.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And possibly maybe, her sons and her daughters would have been on there, but that never happened.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
